Git-Flow Explained Simply (Layman First → Interview Level Later)
1️⃣ Layman Explanation (Very Simple)

Imagine a software project like building a car in a factory 🚗.

You don’t build everything directly in the showroom. Instead, you have different work areas.

Main branch → The showroom car (stable version customers see).

Develop branch → The factory assembly line where new parts are added.

Feature branches → Engineers building individual parts like engine, doors, wheels.

Release branch → Final testing area before sending the car to the showroom.

Hotfix branch → Emergency repair when a car in the showroom has a problem.

This workflow is called Git Flow, used with Git.

